text: Ramvik is a locality in Västernorrland County in Sweden. In 2010, 691 people lived there. The locality is bimunicipal. That means it spans across the borderlines of two municipalities (Härnösand Municipality and Kramfors Municipality). Ramvik was the home of Swedish politician Thorbjörn Fälldin. == References == Category:Settlements in Vasternorrland County
title: Ramvik
